   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "title: Black-Scholes\n",
    "author: Prabhav Shetty\n",
    "date: 2026-05-22\n",
    "categories:\n",
    "  - derivatives\n",
    "  - options\n",
    "  - code\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## The Concept \n",
    "The classic Black-Scholes-Merton partial differential equation solves for a derivative's price under strict assumptions: $$ \\frac{\\partial V}{\\partial t} + \\frac{1}{2}\\sigma^2 S^2 \\frac{\\partial^2 V}{\\partial S^2} + r S \\frac{\\partial V}{\\partial S} - rV = 0 $$ Let's quickly plot the option Greeks dynamically using Python to see how Delta changes relative to asset price.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Python Implementation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "9296471c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 672x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 449,
       "width": 588
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np \n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt \n",
    "from scipy.stats import norm \n",
    "\n",
    "def bs_delta(S, K, T, r, sigma):\n",
    "\td1 = (np.log(S / K) + (r + 0.5 * sigma ** 2) * T) / (sigma * np.sqrt(T))\n",
    "\treturn norm.cdf(d1) \n",
    "\t\n",
    "S_space = np.linspace(80, 120, 100) \n",
    "deltas = [bs_delta(S, K=100, T=0.5, r=0.05, sigma=0.2) for S in S_space] \n",
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(S_space, deltas, label='Delta', color='blue') \n",
    "plt.axvline(100, color='red', linestyle='--', label='Strike (K=100)')\n",
    "plt.title(\"Option Delta vs Asset Price\") \n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Stock Price\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Delta\") \n",
    "plt.legend() \n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  }
 ],
